In general:
- Do not create .md files unless specifically asked
- Write succinct code
- Write terse documentation
- Keep comments to the top of the function unless doing something very tricky

When writing SystemVerilog:
- No need to align input/output names. Just leave one space
- Use wire/assign instead of logic/always_comb for small stuff. Only use logic/always_comb if wire/assign gets too gnarly
- Use always_comb and always_ff instead of just "always"
- Don't use "reg". either wire or logic

When writing Python:
- Do not try/catch. Let the program crash
- Keep docstrings to one line where possible
- Make use of typing
- Make use of assert (instead of if/throw)

When writing cocotb tests:
- We are on cocotb 2.0.1. use unit= instead of units=
- Use value.to_unsigned() instead of value.integer
